combsleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cornu","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Heloise.","French: from Old French <i>corne</i> ‘horn’ (from Late Latin <i>corna</i>), an unflattering nickname for a cuckold, or a metonymic occupational name for a hornblower or worker in horn.","English (Middlesex): variant of   Corn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Corneau","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alcide, Cecile, Normand, Pierre, Yvon.","French: from a diminutive of Old French <i>corne</i> ‘horn’ (see   Corne  )."]},{"name":"Corn","meanings":["English: nickname from Old English <i>corn</i>, a metathesized form of <i>cran</i> ‘crane’ (see   Crane  ).","English: metonymic occupational name for a maker or user of hand mills, Old English <i>cweorn</i>.","Americanized form of German, Dutch, Czech, or Jewish   Korn  , or a shortened form of any of the composite names formed with this element."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Cornu was born in 1257, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir William de Doddiscombe. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1257–":"1257–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1275–1330":"1275–1330","1257–Female":"1257–Surnud","1257":"1257","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Doddiscombsleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Doddiscombsleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1257–":"1257–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1275–1330":"1275–1330","1257–Female":"1257–Kuollut","1257":"1257","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Doddiscombsleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Doddiscombsleigh, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1257–":"1257–Décédée","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1275–1330":"1275–1330","1257–Female":"1257–Décédée","1257":"1257","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Doddiscombsleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Doddiscombsleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Cornu est née en 1257, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir William de Doddiscombe. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1257–":"1257–Verstorben","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","1275–1330":"1275–1330","1257–Female":"1257–Verstorben","1257":"1257","1275":"1275","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, England, United Kingdom"